{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":884,"text":"\"Where are you from?\"\nsaid the pale, tattooed man."},{"time":7583,"text":"\"Where are you from?\""},{"time":12453,"text":"It's September 21, 2001,"},{"time":16533,"text":"10 days after the worst attack\non America since World War II."},{"time":22715,"text":"Everyone wonders about the next plane."},{"time":26940,"text":"People are looking for scapegoats."},{"time":30762,"text":"The president, \nthe night before, pledges to"},{"time":34490,"text":"\"bring our enemies to justice \nor bring justice to our enemies.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":40934,"text":"And in the Dallas mini-mart,"},{"time":46493,"text":"a Dallas mini-part surrounded\nby tire shops and strip joints"},{"time":52266,"text":"a Bangladeshi immigrant \nworks the register."},{"time":56273,"text":"Back home, Raisuddin Bhuiyan\nwas a big man, an Air Force officer."},{"time":63315,"text":"But he dreamed of a \nfresh start in America."},{"time":66919,"text":"If he had to work briefly in a mini-mart\nto save up for I.T. classes"},{"time":72217,"text":"and his wedding in two months, so be it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75605,"text":"Then, on September 21, \nthat tattooed man enters the mart."},{"time":80785,"text":"He holds a shotgun."},{"time":84496,"text":"Raisuddin knows the drill:"},{"time":86159,"text":"puts cash on the counter."},{"time":90058,"text":"This time, the man doesn't \ntouch the money."},{"time":94519,"text":"\"Where are you from?\" he asks."},{"time":98990,"text":"\"Excuse me?\" Raisuddin answers."},{"time":104192,"text":"His accent betrays him."},{"time":108317,"text":"The tattooed man, a self-styled\ntrue American vigilante,"},{"time":113334,"text":"shoots Raisuddin in revenge for 9/11."},{"time":118083,"text":"Raisuddin feels millions of bees\nstinging his face."},{"time":123982,"text":"In fact, dozens of scalding, \nbirdshot pellets puncture his head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130279,"text":"Behind the counter, he lays in blood."},{"time":133859,"text":"He cups a hand over his forehead\nto keep in the brains"},{"time":138350,"text":"on which he'd gambled everything."},{"time":142298,"text":"He recites verses from the Koran,\nbegging his God to live."},{"time":148857,"text":"He senses he is dying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153172,"text":"He didn't die."},{"time":155690,"text":"His right eye left him."},{"time":159006,"text":"His fianc√©e left him."},{"time":162591,"text":"His landlord, the mini-mart owner,\nkicked him out."},{"time":166691,"text":"Soon he was homeless and \n60,000 dollars in medical debt,"},{"time":172004,"text":"including a fee for dialing \nfor an ambulance."},{"time":177996,"text":"But Raisuddin lived."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180458,"text":"And years later, he would ask\nwhat he could do to repay his God"},{"time":186453,"text":"and become worthy of this second chance."},{"time":189792,"text":"He would come to believe, in fact,"},{"time":191883,"text":"that this chance called for him\nto give a second chance"},{"time":197611,"text":"to a man we might think\ndeserved no chance at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203544,"text":"Twelve years ago, I was a fresh graduate\nseeking my way in the world."},{"time":209632,"text":"Born in Ohio to Indian immigrants,\n"},{"time":212132,"text":"I settled on the ultimate rebellion \nagainst my parents,"},{"time":215399,"text":"moving to the country they had worked\nso damn hard to get out of."},{"time":220429,"text":"What I thought might be a six-month stint\nin Mumbai stretched to six years."},{"time":226020,"text":"I became a writer and found myself\namid a magical story:"},{"time":230665,"text":"the awakening of hope across much\nof the so-called Third World."},{"time":235182,"text":"Six years ago, I returned to America\nand realized something:"},{"time":240238,"text":"The American Dream was thriving,"},{"time":243302,"text":"but only in India."},{"time":246825,"text":"In America, not so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250270,"text":"In fact, I observed that \nAmerica was fracturing"},{"time":254093,"text":"into two distinct societies:"},{"time":256327,"text":"a republic of dreams\nand a republic of fears."},{"time":260966,"text":"And then, I stumbled onto this \nincredible tale of two lives"},{"time":264317,"text":"and of these two Americas that brutally\ncollided in that Dallas mini-mart."},{"time":271640,"text":"I knew at once I wanted to learn more,"},{"time":274041,"text":"and eventually that I would write\na book about them,"},{"time":276812,"text":"for their story was the story \nof America's fracturing"},{"time":280694,"text":"and of how it might be put back together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286280,"text":"After he was shot, Raisuddin's life\ngrew no easier."},{"time":290260,"text":"The day after admitting him,\nthe hospital discharged him."},{"time":294960,"text":"His right eye couldn't see."},{"time":296938,"text":"He couldn't speak."},{"time":298546,"text":"Metal peppered his face."},{"time":301665,"text":"But he had no insurance, \nso they bounced him."},{"time":305846,"text":"His family in Bangladesh \nbegged him, \"Come home.\""},{"time":311070,"text":"But he told them he had \na dream to see about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315148,"text":"He found telemarketing work,"},{"time":317699,"text":"then he became an Olive Garden waiter,"},{"time":320974,"text":"because where better to get over his fear\nof white people than the Olive Garden?"},{"time":325094,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":328434,"text":"Now, as a devout Muslim,\nhe refused alcohol,"},{"time":332991,"text":"didn't touch the stuff."},{"time":335188,"text":"Then he learned that not selling it\nwould slash his pay."},{"time":340215,"text":"So he reasoned, like a budding \nAmerican pragmatist,"},{"time":344006,"text":"\"Well, God wouldn't want me\nto starve, would he?\""},{"time":348138,"text":"And before long, in some months, \nRaisuddin was that Olive Garden's"},{"time":351406,"text":"highest grossing alcohol pusher."},{"time":355477,"text":"He found a man who taught him\ndatabase administration."},{"time":359364,"text":"He got part-time I.T. gigs."},{"time":361486,"text":"Eventually, he landed a six-figure job\nat a blue chip tech company in Dallas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368048,"text":"But as America began\nto work for Raisuddin,"},{"time":372816,"text":"he avoided the classic\nerror of the fortunate:"},{"time":376853,"text":"assuming you're the rule, \nnot the exception."},{"time":380777,"text":"In fact, he observed that many with\nthe fortune of being born American"},{"time":386576,"text":"were nonetheless trapped in lives that \nmade second chances like his impossible."},{"time":393298,"text":"He saw it at the Olive Garden itself,"},{"time":396729,"text":"where so many of his colleagues had\nchildhood horror stories"},{"time":400239,"text":"of family dysfunction, chaos, \naddiction, crime."},{"time":404956,"text":"He'd heard a similar tale about\nthe man who shot him"},{"time":409407,"text":"back when he attended his trial."},{"time":412059,"text":"The closer Raisuddin got to the America\nhe had coveted from afar,"},{"time":417789,"text":"the more he realized there was\nanother, equally real, America"},{"time":421973,"text":"that was stingier with second chances."},{"time":427595,"text":"The man who shot Raisuddin grew up\nin that stingier America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433890,"text":"From a distance, Mark Stroman\nwas always the spark of parties,"},{"time":438980,"text":"always making girls feel pretty."},{"time":442543,"text":"Always working, no matter what \ndrugs or fights he'd had the night before."},{"time":447139,"text":"But he'd always wrestled with demons."},{"time":451244,"text":"He entered the world through\nthe three gateways"},{"time":453749,"text":"that doom so many young American men:"},{"time":456471,"text":"bad parents, bad schools, bad prisons."},{"time":461340,"text":"His mother told him, regretfully, as a boy\n"},{"time":464871,"text":"that she'd been just 50 dollars \nshort of aborting him."},{"time":470214,"text":"Sometimes, that little boy \nwould be at school,"},{"time":476078,"text":"he'd suddenly pull a knife \non his fellow classmates."},{"time":480579,"text":"Sometimes that same little boy\nwould be at his grandparents',"},{"time":484187,"text":"tenderly feeding horses."},{"time":486934,"text":"He was getting arrested before he shaved,"},{"time":489379,"text":"first juvenile, then prison."},{"time":491805,"text":"He became a casual white supremacist"},{"time":494944,"text":"and, like so many around him, \na drug-addled and absent father."},{"time":500656,"text":"And then, before long,\nhe found himself on death row,"},{"time":505564,"text":"for in his 2001 counter-jihad, \nhe had shot not one mini-mart clerk,"},{"time":511688,"text":"but three."},{"time":513596,"text":"Only Raisuddin survived."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516944,"text":"Strangely, death row was \nthe first institution"},{"time":521808,"text":"that left Stroman better."},{"time":525341,"text":"His old influences quit him."},{"time":527569,"text":"The people entering his life \nwere virtuous and caring:"},{"time":531225,"text":"pastors, journalists, European pen-pals."},{"time":535989,"text":"They listened to him, prayed with him,\nhelped him question himself."},{"time":542282,"text":"And sent him on a journey \nof introspection and betterment."},{"time":547428,"text":"He finally faced the hatred \nthat had defined his life."},{"time":552362,"text":"He read Viktor Frankl, \nthe Holocaust survivor"},{"time":555253,"text":"and regretted his swastika tattoos."},{"time":558633,"text":"He found God."},{"time":560925,"text":"Then one day in 2011, \n10 years after his crimes,"},{"time":565152,"text":"Stroman received news."},{"time":567591,"text":"One of the men he'd shot, the survivor,\nwas fighting to save his life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575384,"text":"You see, late in 2009,\neight years after that shooting,"},{"time":581173,"text":"Raisuddin had gone on his own journey,\na pilgrimage to Mecca."},{"time":587196,"text":"Amid its crowds, \nhe felt immense gratitude,"},{"time":591450,"text":"but also duty."},{"time":593245,"text":"He recalled promising God, \nas he lay dying in 2001,"},{"time":597034,"text":"that if he lived, he would serve \nhumanity all his days."},{"time":602234,"text":"Then, he'd gotten busy \nrelaying the bricks of a life."},{"time":607529,"text":"Now it was time to pay his debts."},{"time":611982,"text":"And he decided, upon reflection,\nthat his method of payment"},{"time":615872,"text":"would be an intervention \nin the cycle of vengeance"},{"time":619135,"text":"between the Muslim and Western worlds."},{"time":621994,"text":"And how would he intervene?"},{"time":624689,"text":"By forgiving Stroman publicly\nin the name of Islam"},{"time":628991,"text":"and its doctrine of mercy."},{"time":630731,"text":"And then suing the state of Texas\nand its governor Rick Perry"},{"time":637292,"text":"to prevent them from executing Stroman,"},{"time":640997,"text":"exactly like most people \nshot in the face do."},{"time":644111,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":646475,"text":"Yet Raisuddin's mercy was inspired \nnot only by faith."},{"time":653701,"text":"A newly minted American citizen,\nhe had come to believe that Stroman"},{"time":659759,"text":"was the product of a hurting America that\ncouldn't just be lethally injected away."},{"time":666739,"text":"That insight is what moved me \nto write my book \"The True American.\""},{"time":671204,"text":"This immigrant begging America \nto be as merciful to a native son"},{"time":675851,"text":"as it had been to an adopted one."},{"time":680768,"text":"In the mini-mart, all those years earlier,"},{"time":683621,"text":"not just two men, \nbut two Americas collided."},{"time":688047,"text":"An America that still dreams, \nstill strives,"},{"time":690968,"text":"still imagines that tomorrow\ncan build on today,"},{"time":695047,"text":"and an America that has resigned to fate,"},{"time":698146,"text":"buckled under stress and chaos,\nlowered expectations,"},{"time":701280,"text":"an ducked into the oldest of refuges:"},{"time":704418,"text":"the tribal fellowship of one's\nown narrow kind."},{"time":708218,"text":"And it was Raisuddin, despite\nbeing a newcomer,"},{"time":710888,"text":"despite being attacked,\n"},{"time":712215,"text":"despite being homeless and traumatized,"},{"time":715088,"text":"who belonged to that republic of dreams"},{"time":718492,"text":"and Stroman who belonged to that \nother wounded country,"},{"time":723103,"text":"despite being born with the privilege\nof a native white man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728418,"text":"I realized these men's stories formed\nan urgent parable about America."},{"time":734704,"text":"The country I am so proud to call my own"},{"time":738723,"text":"wasn't living through a \ngeneralized decline"},{"time":742589,"text":"as seen in Spain or Greece, \nwhere prospects were dimming for everyone."},{"time":749683,"text":"America is simultaneously the most\nand the least successful country"},{"time":754680,"text":"in the industrialized world."},{"time":757027,"text":"Launching the world's best companies,"},{"time":759571,"text":"even as record numbers \nof children go hungry."},{"time":762970,"text":"Seeing life-expectancy drop\nfor large groups,"},{"time":767125,"text":"even as it polishes \nthe world's best hospitals."},{"time":770831,"text":"America today is a sprightly young body,"},{"time":775134,"text":"hit by one of those strokes \nthat sucks the life from one side,"},{"time":780952,"text":"while leaving the other\nworryingly perfect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785430,"text":"On July 20, 2011, right after \na sobbing Raisuddin"},{"time":792056,"text":"testified in defense of Stroman's life,"},{"time":794355,"text":"Stroman was killed by lethal injection\nby the state he so loved."},{"time":800679,"text":"Hours earlier, when Raisuddin still\nthought he could still save Stroman,"},{"time":805232,"text":"the two men got to speak \nfor the second time ever."},{"time":808200,"text":"Here is an excerpt from their phone call."},{"time":811592,"text":"Raisuddin: \"Mark, you should know \nthat I am praying for God,"},{"time":817450,"text":"the most compassionate and gracious."},{"time":820493,"text":"I forgive you and I do not hate you."},{"time":822961,"text":"I never hated you.\""},{"time":825952,"text":"Stroman: \"You are a remarkable person."},{"time":830396,"text":"Thank you from my heart."},{"time":832513,"text":"I love you, bro.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":835400,"text":"Even more amazingly, after the execution,\n"},{"time":839318,"text":"Raisuddin reached out to Stroman's \neldest daughter, Amber,"},{"time":843530,"text":"an ex-convinct and an addict."},{"time":846273,"text":"and offered his help."},{"time":848060,"text":"\"You may have lost a father,\"\nhe told her,"},{"time":851058,"text":"\"but you've gained an uncle.\""},{"time":854600,"text":"He wanted her, too, to have \na second chance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860483,"text":"If human history were a parade,"},{"time":865618,"text":"America's float would be \na neon shrine to second chances."},{"time":872325,"text":"But America, generous with second chances\nto the children of other lands,"},{"time":878025,"text":"today grows miserly with first chances\nto the children of its own."},{"time":884241,"text":"America still dazzles at allowing\nanybody to become an American."},{"time":889168,"text":"But it is losing its luster at allowing\nevery American to become a somebody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895811,"text":"Over the last decade, seven million\nforeigners gained American citizenship."},{"time":900583,"text":"Remarkable."},{"time":902607,"text":"In the meanwhile, how many Americans\ngained a place in the middle class?"},{"time":907912,"text":"Actually, the net influx was negative."},{"time":911682,"text":"Go back further, \nand it's even more striking:"},{"time":913981,"text":"Since the 60s, the middle class\nhas shrunk by 20 percent,"},{"time":919212,"text":"mainly because of the people\ntumbling out of it."},{"time":922564,"text":"And my reporting around the country\ntells me the problem is grimmer"},{"time":926226,"text":"than simple inequality."},{"time":928639,"text":"What I observe is a pair of secessions\nfrom the unifying center of American life."},{"time":934574,"text":"An affluent secession of up, up and away,"},{"time":938102,"text":"into elite enclaves of the educated\nand into a global matrix"},{"time":941534,"text":"of work, money and connections,"},{"time":944317,"text":"and an impoverished secession \nof down and out"},{"time":948415,"text":"into disconnected, dead-end lives"},{"time":951159,"text":"that the fortunate scarcely see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955183,"text":"And don't console yourself \nthat you are the 99 percent."},{"time":961918,"text":"If you live near a Whole Foods,"},{"time":966504,"text":"if no one in your family serves \nin the military,"},{"time":970167,"text":"if you're paid by the year,\nnot the hour,"},{"time":975386,"text":"if most people you know finished college,"},{"time":978783,"text":"if no one you know uses meth,"},{"time":981105,"text":"if you married once and remain married,"},{"time":983285,"text":"if you're not one of 65 million Americans\nwith a criminal record --"},{"time":987627,"text":"if any or all of these things \ndescribe you,"},{"time":991409,"text":"then accept the possibility that actually,"},{"time":994276,"text":"you may not know what's going on"},{"time":996699,"text":"and you may be part of the problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002588,"text":"Other generations had to build \na fresh society after slavery,"},{"time":1008576,"text":"pull through a depression,\ndefeat fascism,"},{"time":1012840,"text":"freedom-ride in Mississippi."},{"time":1015569,"text":"The moral challenge of \nmy generation, I believe,"},{"time":1018096,"text":"is to reacquaint these two Americas,"},{"time":1021213,"text":"to choose union over secession once again."},{"time":1026392,"text":"This ins't a problem we can tax\nor tax-cut away."},{"time":1030337,"text":"It won't be solved by tweeting harder,\nbuilding slicker apps,"},{"time":1034527,"text":"or starting one more \nartisanal coffee roasting service."},{"time":1038965,"text":"It is a moral challenge that begs \neach of us in the flourishing America"},{"time":1045232,"text":"to take on the wilting America as our own,"},{"time":1049327,"text":"as Raisuddin tried to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1052342,"text":"Like him, we can make pilgrimages."},{"time":1054923,"text":"And there, in Baltimore and Oregon \nand Appalachia,"},{"time":1058446,"text":"find new purpose, as he did."},{"time":1060938,"text":"We can immerse ourselves \nin that other country,"},{"time":1064197,"text":"bear witness to its hopes and sorrows,"},{"time":1067974,"text":"and, like Raisuddin, ask what we can do."},{"time":1074829,"text":"What can you do?"},{"time":1077955,"text":"What can you do?"},{"time":1079706,"text":"What can we do?"},{"time":1081679,"text":"How might we build \na more merciful country?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1086726,"text":"We, the greatest inventors in the world,\n"},{"time":1090933,"text":"can invent solutions to the problems \nof that America, not only our own."},{"time":1095948,"text":"We, the writers and the journalists, \ncan cover that America's stories,"},{"time":1099350,"text":"instead of shutting down \nbureaus in its midst."},{"time":1102946,"text":"We can finance that America's ideas,"},{"time":1106190,"text":"instead of ideas from New York \nand San Francisco."},{"time":1109405,"text":"We can put our stethoscopes to its backs,"},{"time":1112250,"text":"teach there, go to court there,\nmake there, live there, pray there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1118475,"text":"This, I believe, is the calling \nof a generation."},{"time":1123272,"text":"An America whose two halves learn again\n"},{"time":1126758,"text":"to stride, to plow, to forge,\nto dare together."},{"time":1134374,"text":"A republic of chances, rewoven, renewed,"},{"time":1140099,"text":"begins with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1143777,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1145616,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}